  "text": "Immunofluorescent staining and in situ TUNEL assay Cells were fixed as described [CITATION_1] . For immunofluorescent staining, the fixed cells were incubated with a 1:500 dilution of the anti-HA antibody and a 1:200 dilution of the anti-MicLH antibody in blocking solution (3% BSA, 10% Goat Serum, 0.1% Tween 20 in PBS), followed by incubation with a 1:1000 dilution of Alexa 488-conjugated anti-mouse IgG and Alexa 568-conjugated anti-rabbit IgG. For the in situ TUNEL assay, the fixed cells were incubated with 0.3% Triton X-100 in PBS and then with the TUNEL reaction mix (In situ Cell Death Detection Kit, Roche) at 37 C for 4 hours. The cells were subsequently incubated with a 1:500 dilution of the anti-HA antibody in blocking solution, followed by incubation with a 1:1000 dilution of Alexa 568-conjugated anti-mouse IgG. The samples were finally counter-stained with 10 ng/ml DAPI.",
